The paper deals with the construction of initial T-algebras and final T-coalgebras, which are concepts from category theory. It also discusses the interpretation of recursive datatypes in programming semantics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also deals with abstract constructions and compositionality principles, which are topics in category theory and algebra. Hence, it could also belong to cs.CT (Computational Topology), cs.PL (Programming Languages), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the paper discusses the comparison of its methods with other approaches from the literature, which could place it in cs.IT (Information Theory).
